1) This gene codes for an ATPase in Salmonella, which is important for using energy in the cell.
ATPase is necessary for breaking down the cell's energy supply (ATP) so that energy
can be used to drive other chemical reactions in the cell.

2,3) Both sequences code for an SPI-1 secretion system protein, which the bacteria uses to affect other cells of different
organisms (which makes some salmonella pathogenic).

4,5) Codes for a secretion system export protein, which is one of the proteins that the bacteria uses to invade host
organisms.

Based on all of these proteins, the function of this gene is most likely for attacking and invading host cell's, and
codes for proteins that are necessary for transporting the bacteria's material into its targets to take over.
